<title>SOUTH AFRICA: IBM South Africa year earnings slump.</title>
<headline>IBM South Africa year earnings slump.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-02-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended December 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, headline (cts)   55.8	  vs 69.4</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     49.1	  vs 67.2</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 26.0	  vs 26.0</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   73.8	  vs 101.0</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   118.0	 vs 160.3</p>
<p>    Tax			 49.0	  vs 60.8</p>
<p>    Operating income	102.1	 vs 150.9</p>
<p>Goodwill/trademark</p>
<p>     written off	    14.6	  vs 3.3</p>
<p>    Investment income     30.5	  vs 12.7</p>
<p>    Total revenue	   1,981.6     vs 1,911.3</p>
<p>     - hardware	     1,079.6     vs 1,124.6</p>
<p>     - software	     416.7	 vs 431.0</p>
<p>     - maintenance	  200.7	 vs 189.4</p>
<p>     - service		284.6	 vs 166.3</p>
<p>Div payable April 21</p>
<p>on register March 14</p>
<p>Full name: IBM South Africa Group Ltd</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
